 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Written in Winter.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Now o'er the fading landscape all around</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">His silver mantle hoary Winter spreads:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">No more the groves with melody resound,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">No cheerful herbage crowns the lonely meads.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Bleak blows the wind o'er yon deserted plain;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">While lowering clouds obscure the wintry sky,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And sickening Nature sees with tender pain</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The flowery progeny of Summer die.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="sestarima">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thus, in warm youth, vain Beauty's fleeting power</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Charms for a moment Love's fantastic eye;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Old Age or Sickness crops the short-liv'd flower,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And wither'd all its brightest honours lie.</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But Virtue, arm'd against Time's rudest blast,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Shall, like the laurel, ever verdant last.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
